Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. guilty by jury

Motion in Limine received by the court but not filed.  State does not oppose.  Court grants the motion for the videos.  No miranda or goodchild issues.  Court accepts the statement from the defense.  Note taking to be allowed.  Defense does not have a list of witness, State hands in his list of witnesses to the court.  State is not going to bring the deft prior record.  Sequestration is ordered and agreed to by the court.   Take a break and check with the jury clerk.
Case recalled. Apeparances the same. Clerk: Dunbar. Jury selection. Completed @ 10 am. Sidebar placed on the record. 

There are 31 jurors that are here.  Might be a issue with 3 jurors.  The one juror with the hearing issue can hear in the courtroom but not in the jury room.  Back on the reacord 10:10 am.  Bailiff's updates the State/Defense.  

Juror in court 10:20 am.  Court reads the preliminary jury instructions.  Opening statements completed at 11:03 am.  State to call first witness:
Rick Webster  duly sworn and testifies. Id'd deft.  Vernon Semd   duly sworn and testifies.  Id'd Deft  Dustin Meunier  duly sworn and testifies.  Sidebar at 11:58 am - Discovery question; Sidebar 12:01 p State's questioning  Jurors excused at 12:05 pm for lunch back at 1:15 pm.

Back from lunch at 1:15 pm Thomas Barker duly sworn and testifies.  Sidebar 1:27 - question from State.  State rests 1:32 pm  Break to give time for the defense to talk about testifing.  The deft has decided not to testify.  Court advises the deft of his rights.  FVI  Jurors back 1:55 pm  Defense will not be calling any witnesses.  Off the record jury instuction meeting.  Back on the record 2:23 pm Jurors back 2:27 pm  Closings complete 3:00 pm.  Jurors excused 3:10 until we get the courtroom ready for the jurors.  Was instructed there was a verdict at 3:30 pm.  Everyone is back in the courtroom.  The jurors are brought back into the court 3:41 pm.  Court reads the verdict of guilty.  Jurors are polled.

State requests a PSI - defense objects.  Defense is ready to do sentencing.  Discussions on the sentencing.  Court takes a break until 4:05 pm.  Court orders a PSI.  

Court also revokes bond and remands the deft to Lincoln Hills.  Defense attorney also wants to put on the record that she objects to Lincoln County DOC doing the PSI.
